rComments: She's as nice as everyone says. She even pushed a paper forward because a bunch of us had too many other tests scheduled the same weeks as it. In terms of the course, it's great even for people new to philosophy. Her material is comprehensive but not overwhelming. The ONLY con is that her communication with the TAs seems to be sub-par.

She was always available whenever I needed help.  Provided great lectures and was very understanding and caring.   I was very lucky to have her as my professor.   Thank you Professor Ross!!!  Truly Profess(i)o(nal)r.

Probably one of the most caring Profs I've ever had. She's always down to help you out, so don't be afraid to see her in office hours. Always kind and highly approachable, I felt like she had my back and that took a lot of stress out of the course. Love ya Amber!

Amazing amazing amazing professor and lovely human being. Really cared for her students and went out of her way to engage with them. She put a real effort into breaking down tough concepts and answering questions. Bravo.

A brilliant professor; lectures are very engaging and always explicate confusing concepts. My only complaint about the course structure was that I felt too much emphasis was put on participation markstutorials, as they made up a huge chunk of our final grade. Not exactly a "negative" though, as other students may prefer such a learning style.
